Overview

This file documents the analyses pediatric urobiome project presented in Figure 2: The pediatric urobiome composition varies by sex and age.

For these analyses, the age was restricted to children less than 60 months.

Set-up

Library libraries, workspace

library(here)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(DT)

library(phyloseq)

library(patchwork)

load(here("data", "cairibu_data_blca_tree.RData"))

Figure 2A. Microshades plot by sex

ps_500r_blca_human <-ps_500r_blca_human %>%
  subset_samples(age_months <= 60) %>% 
  tax_glom( taxrank = "species", NArm = FALSE)

mdf_s <- ps_500r_blca_human  %>% 
  transform_sample_counts(function(x) x / sum(x) ) %>% 
  psmelt() 


color_dfs <- create_color_dfs(mdf_s, group_level = "phylum",subgroup_level = "species")

color_dfs_ordered <- reorder_samples_by(color_dfs$mdf, color_dfs$cdf, group_level = "phylum",
                                        subgroup_level = "species", order_tax = "Firmicutes", 
                                        sink_abundant_groups = FALSE, sample_variable = "place")

new_legend <- custom_legend(color_dfs$mdf, color_dfs$cdf, group_level = "phylum",subgroup_level = "species")
                                     
plot_1 <- plot_microshades(color_dfs_ordered$mdf,color_dfs_ordered$cdf, group_label = "Phylum Species", x = "place") +
  facet_grid(~sex, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +
  ggtitle("Urinary barplot by sex")  + 
  theme(legend.position = "none")

mdf_s <- color_dfs_ordered$mdf

plot_grid(plot_1, new_legend, rel_widths = c(1, .4))

Supplemental Figure S2. Contribution plots by sex

female_contributions <- plot_contributions(color_dfs_ordered$mdf,color_dfs_ordered$cdf, "sex", "Female")

male_contributions <- plot_contributions(color_dfs_ordered$mdf,color_dfs_ordered$cdf, "sex", "Male")

female_contributions$box +ylim(0,1) + male_contributions$box +ylim(0,1) +theme(axis.title.y=element_blank(), axis.text.y= element_blank(), axis.ticks.y=element_blank())

Figure 2B. relative abundance of specific taxa

mdf_g <- ps_500r_blca_human %>% 
  tax_glom( taxrank = "genus", NArm = FALSE) %>% 
  transform_sample_counts(function(x) x / sum(x) ) %>% 
  psmelt()

color_df_g <- create_color_dfs(mdf_g, group_level = "phylum",subgroup_level = "genus")

groups <- color_df_g$cdf$group
taxa_results_g <- data.frame(group = NA, pval=NA)

for (i in 1:length(groups)){
  
  subset <- color_df_g$mdf %>% filter(group == groups[i])
  test_results <- wilcox.test(Abundance~sex, data = subset)
  taxa_results_g <- rbind(taxa_results_g, c(groups[i], round(test_results$p.value,4)))
}

keep_taxa <- grepl("Other", taxa_results_g$group)

taxa_results_g <- taxa_results_g %>% filter(!keep_taxa)
taxa_results_g %>% datatable(rownames = FALSE)
# genus-level
taxa_results_g <- taxa_results_g %>% filter(pval <= 0.05)

color_df_g$mdf %>% filter(group %in% taxa_results_g$group) %>% ggplot(aes(x= genus,y =Abundance, fill=sex)) + geom_boxplot() + coord_flip()

Figure 2C. Alpha diversity by sex

metrics <-  c('observed', 'shannon', 'inverse_simpson','pielou')
results_alpha <-  microbiome::alpha(ps_500r_blca_human, index = metrics)
results_alpha_cols <- c(colnames(results_alpha), "age_months", "sex")

meta_data <- data.frame(sample_data(ps_500r_blca_human))
results_alpha <- merge(meta_data, results_alpha, by = "row.names")

results_alpha$Row.names <- NULL

results_alpha_temp <- results_alpha %>% select(!!(results_alpha_cols)) %>% 
  rename("shannon"= "diversity_shannon", "inverse_simpson" ="diversity_inverse_simpson", "pielou"="evenness_pielou") 

results_alpha_long <- results_alpha_temp %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("observed","shannon", "inverse_simpson", "pielou" ), values_to = "alpha_value", names_to = "alpha_metric")

plot_alpha <-  results_alpha_long %>%
  ggplot( aes_string(x = "sex", y = "alpha_value", color = "alpha_metric")) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  #theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  facet_wrap(~alpha_metric, scales="free", nrow = 1)

  plot_alpha

wilcox.test(diversity_inverse_simpson ~ sex, data = results_alpha)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum exact test
## 
## data:  diversity_inverse_simpson by sex
## W = 114, p-value = 0.05232
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
wilcox.test(diversity_shannon ~ sex, data = results_alpha)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum exact test
## 
## data:  diversity_shannon by sex
## W = 116, p-value = 0.0398
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
wilcox.test(evenness_pielou ~ sex, data = results_alpha)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum exact test
## 
## data:  evenness_pielou by sex
## W = 96, p-value = 0.3475
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
wilcox.test(observed ~ sex, data = results_alpha)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  observed by sex
## W = 107.5, p-value = 0.1141
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0

Correlation of diversity with age

total_results <- data.frame(comparison = NA, alpha_metric = NA, pval=NA, rho=NA)

# age overall observed and shannon - significant
overall_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha$age_months, y=results_alpha$observed, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("overall", "observed", round(overall_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(overall_results$estimate),3)))

overall_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha$age_months, y=results_alpha$diversity_shannon, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("overall", "shannon", round(overall_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(overall_results$estimate),3)))

overall_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha$age_months, y=results_alpha$diversity_inverse_simpson, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("overall", "inv simpson", round(overall_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(overall_results$estimate),3)))

overall_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha$age_months, y=results_alpha$evenness_pielou, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("overall", "pielou", round(overall_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(overall_results$estimate),3)))

# age by sex
results_alpha_f <- results_alpha %>% filter(sex == "Female")
results_alpha_m <- results_alpha %>% filter(sex == "Male")

# female inv simpson and pielou - signinficant
fem_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_f$age_months, y=results_alpha_f$observed, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("female", "observed", round(fem_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(fem_results$estimate),3)))

fem_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_f$age_months, y=results_alpha_f$diversity_shannon, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("female", "shannon", round(fem_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(fem_results$estimate),3)))

fem_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_f$age_months, y=results_alpha_f$diversity_inverse_simpson, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("female", "inv simpson", round(fem_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(fem_results$estimate),3)))

fem_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_f$age_months, y=results_alpha_f$evenness_pielou, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("female", "pielou", round(fem_results$p.value,4), round(as.numeric(fem_results$estimate),3)))


# male observed - significant
m_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_m$age_months, y=results_alpha_m$observed, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("male", "observed", round(m_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(m_results$estimate),3)))

m_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_m$age_months, y=results_alpha_m$diversity_shannon, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("male", "shannon", round(m_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(m_results$estimate),3)))

m_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_m$age_months, y=results_alpha_m$diversity_inverse_simpson, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("male", "inv simpson", round(m_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(m_results$estimate),3)))

m_results <- cor.test(x=results_alpha_m$age_months, y=results_alpha_m$evenness_pielou, method = "spearman")
total_results <- rbind(total_results, c("male", "pielou", round(m_results$p.value,3), round(as.numeric(m_results$estimate),3)))

# display nice table
total_results <- total_results %>% drop_na %>% pivot_wider(names_from = "comparison", values_from = c("pval", "rho"))

total_results %>% datatable(rownames = FALSE)

  ggplot( aes_string(x = "age_months", y = "alpha_value", color = "sex")) +
  geom_point() +
